      <h2>1969: Arboretum Established</h2>
      <p>
        The forest trees found in the Arboretum had not been harvested since
        1904 and in the 1960s prospective loggers found a takeover full of
        possibilities. Faced with the logging threat, the park’s overseers
        realized the importance of transforming the Hill into a protected
        arboretum.
      </p>

      <p>
        In May of 1969, the college board of trustees approved Sehome Hill’s
        status as an arboretum. Initially, 38 acres were set aside for the
        project; then in 1974, 100 acres were officially preserved for arboretum
        land. The Sehome Hill Arboretum Board of Governors was soon established
        to look after the interests of the Hill.
      </p>
